newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia palm oil ends the week down ahead of PORL.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia palm oil ends the week down ahead of PORL.

text.p: PALM OIL FUTURES PALM OIL PHYSICAL
Nov (3rd pos) 1,171 rgt/tonne Sep (south) 1,205 *
Open/Hi/low 1,205/1,206/1,163 Prev close 1,210
Prev settlement 1,189 * sellers prices

PALM OIL FUTURES - The market reversed an earlier firm trend and closed lower on liquidation on talk of a higher August output from MOPGC against forecaster Ivan Wong. Technical selling also emerged Trading was volatile. Players are waiting for PORLA on Monday.
PALM OIL PHYSICAL - Followed the futures and nearby CPOs. RBD palm oil and olein attributed to the bulk of activity.
In his report today, Ivan Wong said that output in August was estimated to rise by 11 percent to 801,000 tonnes, end-August stock at 775,000 tonnes and exports in August at 680,000 tonnes.
Palm Oil Registration and Licensing Authority (PORLA) is scheduled to release the key August crop data at 0430 GMT on Monday, they said.
Plantation houses said that production in August will rise by between five to 10 percent over July. "Now we have just to wait for final data from PORLA on Monday," a dealer said.
Morning sentiment was boosted by an Indian tender and gains in Chicago soyoil futures overnight, traders said.
India's STC is tendering to buy 6,000 tonnes of RBD palm olein for October 5-20 shipment.

"We are waiting whether India's STC will buy more oil after purchasing about 12,000 tonnes in early part of the week," the dealer said. However there were still no results of the Indian tender although the market has already closed.
"Selling emerged actively when they saw third month Nove futures breaking the 1,200 and falling further to a low of 1,163 level," the dealer said.
By the close, November futures closed 18 ringgit down at 1,171 ringgit ($468.87) a tonne after trading between 1,163 and 1,206 ringgit.
Interest among physical was also confined to selected products and nearby CPOs.

Sept (south) crude palm oil was quoted sellers at 1,205 ringgit a tonne after trading from 1,205 to 1,190. Sept (south) saw bids at 1,200. Sept (central) was offered at 1,190 with bids at 1,175. Sept (north) saw offers at 1,185 and bids at 1,170.
Oct (south) crude palm oil was offered at 1,210 ringgit with bids at 1,200. Oct (central) saw offers at 1,197.50 and bids at 1,190 and Nov (north) at 1,215 with bids at 1,205.
In refined products, Sept RBD palmoil was offered at $520 a tonne FOB Malaysia, and Oct/Nov/Dec at $517.50. Sept was traded at $517.50 and $515.
Sept palm olein saw offers at $560, Oct at $552.50 and Nov/Dec at $540. Oct was dealt at $550, and Nov/Dec at $545.
Sept RBD palm stearin was offered at $410, Oct at $415 and Sept/Oct palm fatty acid distillate saw sellers at $340.
